Can I have a ride?

495
00:37:44,080 --> 00:37:45,380
-Where you going?
-I don't care.

496
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:46,799
Get in the truck.

497
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:48,580
So, bye-bye, Jenny.

498
00:37:51,200 --> 00:37:53,160
They sending me to Vietnam.

499
00:37:56,080 --> 00:37:58,110
It's this whole other country.

500
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:02,450
Just hang on a minute.

501
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:06,640
Listen, you promise me
something, okay?

502
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:09,890
Just, if you're ever in trouble,
don't try to be brave. You just run, okay?

503
00:38:10,360 --> 00:38:11,730
Just run away.

504
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:14,240
Okay.

505
00:38:19,080 --> 00:38:20,200
Jenny.

506
00:38:22,160 --> 00:38:24,089
I'll write you all the time.

507
00:38:33,120 --> 00:38:35,609
And just like that, she was gone.

508
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:54,250
You come back safe to me,
do you hear?

509
00:39:36,160 --> 00:39:39,490
Now, they told us that Vietnam
was gonna be very different

510
00:39:40,040 --> 00:39:42,460
from the United States of America.

511
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:47,130
And except for all the beer cans
and the barbecue, it was.

512
00:39:57,440 --> 00:40:00,040
Hey, I bet there's shrimp
all in these waters.

513
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:03,150
They tell me these Vietnams
is good shrimpers.

514
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:06,580
You know, after we win this war,
and we take over everything,

515
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:08,090
we can get American shrimpers

516
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:09,760
to come out here
and shrimp these waters.

517
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:11,370
We'll just shrimp all the time, man.

518
00:40:11,640 --> 00:40:14,339
So much shrimp, why,
you wouldn't believe it.

519
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:16,970
You must be my FNGs.

520
00:40:17,280 --> 00:40:18,290
-Morning, sir!
-Morning, sir!

521
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:20,770
Get your hands down! Do not salute me.

522
00:40:21,160 --> 00:40:22,950
There's goddamn snipers
all around this area

523
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:25,670
who would love to grease an officer.

524
00:40:26,080 --> 00:40:29,029
I'm Lieutenant Dan Taylor.
Welcome to Fourth Platoon.

525
00:40:30,280 --> 00:40:32,310
What's wrong with your lip?

526
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:34,680
I was born with big gums, sir.

527
00:40:35,040 --> 00:40:39,009
Yeah, well, you better tuck that in.
Gonna get that caught on a trip wire.

528
00:40:40,680 --> 00:40:41,839
Where you boys from in the world?

529
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:44,080
-Alabama, sir!
-Alabama, sir!

530
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:46,300
You twins?

531
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:50,510
No, we are not relations, sir.

532
00:40:52,920 --> 00:40:55,410
Look, it's pretty basic here.

533
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:58,590
If you stick with me
and learn from the guys

534
00:40:58,960 --> 00:41:01,210
who've been in country a while,
you'll be all right.

535
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:03,210
There is one item of GI gear

536
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:07,030
that can be the difference between
a live grunt and a dead grunt.

537
00:41:07,840 --> 00:41:10,510
Socks. Cushion sole, OD green.

538
00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:12,040
Try and keep your feet dry.

539
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:13,510
When we're out humping,
I want you boys to remember

540
00:41:13,760 --> 00:41:15,830
to change your socks
whenever we stop.

541
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:18,689
The Mekong will eat a grunt's feet
right off his legs.

542
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:21,049
Sergeant Sims, God damn it,

543
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:22,630
where is that sling rope
I told you to order?

544
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:24,490
I put in the requisitions at Battalion.

545
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:26,480
Yeah, yeah, yeah, well,
you call those sons of bitches again...

546
00:41:26,800 --> 00:41:30,940
Lieutenant Dan sure knew his stuff.
! felt real lucky he was my lieutenant.

547
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:35,149
He was from a long,
great military tradition.

548
00:41:35,760 --> 00:41:38,360
Somebocdy in his family
had fought and died

549
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:43,259
in every single American war.

550
00:41:44,600 --> 00:41:46,319
-God damn it, kick some ass!
-I'm on it, Lieutenant.

551
00:41:46,640 --> 00:41:47,580
Get on it!

552
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:50,640
I guess you could say he had
a lot to live up to.

553
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:56,750
So, you boys are from Arkansas, huh?
Well, I've been through there.

554
00:41:57,400 --> 00:41:59,260
Little Rock's a fine town.

555
00:42:00,120 --> 00:42:03,170
Now, go shake down your gear,
see the platoon sergeant,

556
00:42:03,680 --> 00:42:05,750
draw what you need for the field.

557
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:09,450
If you boys are hungry,
we got steaks burning right over here.

558
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:12,420
Two standing orders in this platoon:

559
00:42:12,840 --> 00:42:15,090
one, take good care of your feet,

560
00:42:15,480 --> 00:42:19,760
two, try not to do anything stupid,
like getting yourself killed.

561
00:42:26,560 --> 00:42:28,310
I sure hope I don't let him down.

562
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:33,720
It wasn't always fun.

563
00:42:34,080 --> 00:42:37,700
Lieutenant Dan was always getting
these funny feelings about a rock,

564
00:42:38,280 --> 00:42:42,560
or a trail, or the road,
so he'd fell us to get down, shut up...

565
00:42:43,240 --> 00:42:44,919
Get down! Shut up!

566
00:42:46,040 --> 00:42:47,230
...SO we did.

567
00:43:04,280 --> 00:43:06,140
Now, I[ don’t know much about anything,

568
00:43:06,480 --> 00:43:09,710
but I think some of America’s
best young men served in this war.

569
00:43:10,240 --> 00:43:12,520
There was Dallas, from Phoenix,

570
00:43:14,480 --> 00:43:16,830
Cleveland, he was from Detroit.

571
00:43:17,240 --> 00:43:19,270
Hey, Tex. Hey, Tex.

572
00:43:19,640 --> 00:43:21,500
Man, what the hell's going on?

573
00:43:21,840 --> 00:43:25,490
And Tex was... Well, 1 don’t remember
where Tex come from.

574
00:43:26,080 --> 00:43:27,380
Nothing.

575
00:43:31,480 --> 00:43:33,620
Fourth Platoon, on your feet.

576
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:37,120
Still got 10 klicks to go to that river.
Move out.

577
00:43:37,640 --> 00:43:39,109
Come on, move out.

578
00:43:41,320 --> 00:43:43,350
Step it up. Look alive out there.

579
00:43:43,720 --> 00:43:47,370
The good thing about Vietnam
is there was always some place to go.

580
00:43:47,960 --> 00:43:49,150
Fire in the hole!

581
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:54,600
Gump, check out that hole.

582
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:57,490
And there was always something to do.

583
00:43:57,920 --> 00:44:00,550
-Mount them up.
-Spread out! Cover his back.

584
00:44:05,800 --> 00:44:10,510
One day, it started raining,
and it didn’t quit for four months.

585
00:44:12,160 --> 00:44:14,580
We'd been through
every kind of rain there is:

586
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:17,170
little bitty stinging rain,

587
00:44:18,160 --> 00:44:20,410
and big old fat rain,

588
00:44:21,160 --> 00:44:23,440
rain that flew in sideways.

589
00:44:23,840 --> 00:44:27,250
And sometimes, rain even seemed
to come straight up from underneath.

590
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:31,440
Shoot, it even rained at night.

591
00:44:32,720 --> 00:44:34,790
-Hey, Forrest.
-Hey, Bubba.

592
00:44:35,160 --> 00:44:37,970
I'm gonna lean up against you.
You just lean right back against me.

593
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:41,670
This way, we don't have to sleep
with our heads in the mud.

594
00:44:43,000 --> 00:44:45,950
You know why we a good partnership,
Forrest?

595
00:44:46,440 --> 00:44:48,540
‘Cause we be watching out
for one another,

596
00:44:48,920 --> 00:44:50,530
like brothers and stuff.

597
00:44:52,640 --> 00:44:55,730
Hey, Forrest, there's something
I've been thinking about.

598
00:44:56,240 --> 00:44:58,770
I got a very important question
to ask you.

599
00:45:00,680 --> 00:45:04,009
How would you like to go
into the shrimping business with me?

600
00:45:05,560 --> 00:45:06,960
Okay.

601
00:45:07,240 --> 00:45:10,149
Man, I tell you what,
I got it all figured out, too.

602
00:45:10,640 --> 00:45:12,990
So many pounds of shrimp
to pay off the boat,

603
00:45:13,400 --> 00:45:16,210
so many pounds for gas,
we can just live right on the boat.

604
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:18,569
We ain't got to pay no rent.

605
00:45:18,960 --> 00:45:20,710
I'll be the captain,
we can just work it together,

606
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:24,620
split everything right down the middle.
Man, I'm telling you, 50-50.

607
00:45:25,200 --> 00:45:28,180
And, hey, Forrest,
all the shrimp you can eat.

608
00:45:30,120 --> 00:45:31,630
That's a fine idea.

609
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:34,670
Bubba did have a fine idea.

610
00:45:38,560 --> 00:45:41,160
leven wrote Jenny
and told her all about it.

611
00:45:42,280 --> 00:45:44,980
! sent her letters,
not every day, but almost.

612
00:45:45,440 --> 00:45:49,650
! told her what ! was doing
and asked her what she was doing,

613
00:45:50,320 --> 00:45:52,600
and told her
how I thought about her always,

614
00:45:54,200 --> 00:45:56,730
and how I was looking forward
to getting a letter from her

615
00:45:57,160 --> 00:45:59,259
just as soon as she had the time.

616
00:46:01,360 --> 00:46:03,460
I'd always let her know that Il was okay.

617
00:46:05,000 --> 00:46:09,420
Then, I'd sign each letter,
"Love, Forrest Gump.”

618
00:46:24,200 --> 00:46:27,359
This one day, we was out walking,
like always,

619
00:46:27,880 --> 00:46:30,370
and then, just like that,

620
00:46:31,600 --> 00:46:34,440
somebody turned off the rain
and the sun come out.

621
00:46:37,720 --> 00:46:39,259
Ambush!

622
00:46:39,960 --> 00:46:41,150
Take cover!

623
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:45,920
Get down!

624
00:46:46,360 --> 00:46:47,590
Quickly!

625
00:46:50,440 --> 00:46:52,190
Get that thing up here, God damn it!

626
00:46:52,520 --> 00:46:54,310
Forrest, you okay?

627
00:46:57,640 --> 00:46:59,850
Strongarm! Strongarm!
Be advised, Strongarm!

628
00:47:00,680 --> 00:47:02,710
Medic, we got a man down!

629
00:47:03,080 --> 00:47:05,540
Strongarm, this is Leg Lima 6, over!

630
00:47:06,600 --> 00:47:09,410
Roger, Strongarm, be advised
we have incoming from the tree line

631
00:47:09,880 --> 00:47:12,860
at points blue plus two.
AKs and rockets...

632
00:47:13,920 --> 00:47:15,390
Misfire! Misfire!

633
00:47:17,920 --> 00:47:19,570
God damn it! Mac!

634
00:47:20,720 --> 00:47:23,629
Get that thing...
Fuck it, get it in the tree line!

635
00:47:24,920 --> 00:47:25,930
Jesus!

636
00:47:26,160 --> 00:47:28,049
My unit is down hard and hurting!

637
00:47:28,400 --> 00:47:31,380
Six are pulling back to Blue Line,
Leg Lima 6 out.

638
00:47:32,560 --> 00:47:34,240
Pull back! Pull back!

639
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:36,310
Run! Run, Forrest!

640
00:47:36,680 --> 00:47:38,640
-Pull back!
-Forrest, Forrest!

641
00:47:39,000 --> 00:47:41,210
Run, man! Run!

642
00:47:41,600 --> 00:47:43,069
Pull back! Run!

643
00:47:45,040 --> 00:47:46,930
Run, God damn it, run!

644
00:48:07,520 --> 00:48:11,380
Medic! Can I get a medic?

645
00:48:12,320 --> 00:48:15,130
! ran and ran, just like Jenny told me to.

646
00:48:18,760 --> 00:48:22,310
Tran so far and so fast
that pretty soon I was all by myself,

647
00:48:22,880 --> 00:48:24,490
which was a bad thing.

648
00:48:25,240 --> 00:48:26,569
Bubba!

649
00:48:28,760 --> 00:48:31,950
Bubba was my best good friend.
! had to make sure that he was okay.

650
00:48:35,960 --> 00:48:37,710
Any friendlies out there?

651
00:48:38,840 --> 00:48:40,700
Yeah, I've got three over here.

652
00:48:41,520 --> 00:48:43,200
Where the hell are you?

653
00:48:44,040 --> 00:48:45,160
Bubba?

654
00:48:46,320 --> 00:48:48,640
And on my way back to find Bubba,

655
00:48:49,040 --> 00:48:51,430
well, there was this boy
laying on the ground.

656
00:48:51,840 --> 00:48:52,850
Tex!

657
00:48:54,960 --> 00:48:55,830
Okay.

658
00:48:56,040 --> 00:48:59,370
! couldn't just let him lay there all alone,
scared the way he was,

659
00:48:59,920 --> 00:49:03,220
so I grabbed him up
and run him out of there.

660
00:49:18,160 --> 00:49:20,230
And every time ! went back
looking for Bubba,

661
00:49:20,600 --> 00:49:23,549
somebody else was saying,
"Help me, Forrest. Help me.”

662
00:49:31,360 --> 00:49:32,940
Can't hear... Can't hear...

663
00:49:35,360 --> 00:49:36,440
No sweat, man. Just lay back.

664
00:49:36,680 --> 00:49:38,779
You'll be okay. You'll be okay.

665
00:49:41,000 --> 00:49:43,560
! started to get scared
that! might never find Bubba.

666
00:49:44,000 --> 00:49:45,050
...OVer.

667
00:49:45,280 --> 00:49:48,050
Roger, Strongarm,
I know my position is danger close.

668
00:49:48,520 --> 00:49:50,060
We got Charlie all over this area.

669
00:49:50,360 --> 00:49:52,320
I gotta have those fast movers
in here now. Over.

670
00:49:52,680 --> 00:49:55,520
-Six, Strongarm, we want...
-Lieutenant Dan, Coleman's dead!

671
00:49:56,000 --> 00:49:57,010
I know he's dead!

672
00:49:57,240 --> 00:49:59,660
My whole goddamn platoon
is wiped out!

673
00:50:00,080 --> 00:50:01,240
-Leg Lima 6, Leg Lima 6.
-God damn it!

674
00:50:01,480 --> 00:50:03,760
-Copy this transmission. Over.
-What are you doing?

675
00:50:04,160 --> 00:50:06,970
Just leave me here! Get away.
Just leave me here! Get out!

676
00:50:07,440 --> 00:50:09,400
Leg Lima 6, Strongarm.
How copy this? Over.

677
00:50:09,760 --> 00:50:11,970
God, I said leave me here, God damn it!

678
00:50:12,360 --> 00:50:15,030
Leg Lima 6, Leg Lima 6,
this is Strongarm, be advised

679
00:50:15,480 --> 00:50:17,160
your fast movers
are inbound at this time, over.

680
00:50:17,480 --> 00:50:20,320
Then, it felt like something
just jumped up and bit me.

681
00:50:21,560 --> 00:50:23,000
Something bit me!

682
00:50:29,800 --> 00:50:31,550
You chink son of a bitch!

683
00:50:34,200 --> 00:50:35,919
I can't leave the platoon.

684
00:50:36,240 --> 00:50:40,419
I told you to leave me there, Gump.
Forget about me. Get yourself out!

685
00:50:41,080 --> 00:50:42,870
Did you hear what I said?

686
00:50:43,840 --> 00:50:45,450
God damn it, put me down!

687
00:50:46,360 --> 00:50:48,110
Get your ass out of here!

688
00:50:51,480 --> 00:50:53,690
I didn't ask you to pull me out of there,
God damn you!

689
00:50:54,080 --> 00:50:55,200
Where the hell
do you think you're going?

690
00:50:55,440 --> 00:50:56,380
To get Bubba.

691
00:50:56,600 --> 00:50:59,860
I got an air strike inbound right now.
They're gonna nape the whole area.

692
00:51:00,400 --> 00:51:02,430
Gump, you stay here, God damn it!
That's an order!

693
00:51:02,800 --> 00:51:04,870
I gotta find Bubba!

694
00:51:20,440 --> 00:51:21,670
Forrest.

695
00:51:29,320 --> 00:51:31,570
-Bubba.
-I'm okay, Forrest.

696
00:51:32,640 --> 00:51:34,040
I'm okay.

697
00:51:41,720 --> 00:51:43,259
Oh, Bubba, no...

698
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:45,490
Nah, I'm gonna be all right.

699
00:51:53,600 --> 00:51:55,810
Come on. Come on. Come on.

700
00:52:00,960 --> 00:52:02,190
I'm okay, Forrest.

701
00:52:03,680 --> 00:52:06,029
I'm okay, man. I'm fine.

702
00:52:41,920 --> 00:52:44,520
Helo's inbound.
Top smoke, get it out there!

703
00:52:45,920 --> 00:52:49,710
If I'd a known this was gonna be the
last time me and Bubba was gonna talk,

704
00:52:50,320 --> 00:52:52,280
I'd of thought of something better to say.

705
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:53,900
Hey, Bubba.

706
00:52:55,120 --> 00:52:56,279
Hey, Forrest.

707
00:52:58,680 --> 00:53:01,419
Forrest, why'd this happen?

708
00:53:03,080 --> 00:53:04,590
You got shot.

709
00:53:06,440 --> 00:53:09,950
Then Bubba said something
! won't ever forget.

710
00:53:11,200 --> 00:53:12,600
I wanna go home.

711
00:53:14,680 --> 00:53:16,430
Bubba was my best good friend.

712
00:53:17,600 --> 00:53:21,430
And even I know that ain't something
you can find just around the corner.

713
00:53:22,040 --> 00:53:24,670
Bubba was gonna be
a shrimping boat captain,

714
00:53:25,120 --> 00:53:28,420
but instead he died right there
by that river in Vietnam.

715
00:53:34,400 --> 00:53:35,940
That's all l have to say about that.

716
00:53:38,840 --> 00:53:40,660
It was a bullet, wasn't it?

717
00:53:43,200 --> 00:53:45,410
-A bullet?
-That jumped up and bit you.

718
00:53:48,040 --> 00:53:49,790
Oh, yes, sir.

719
00:53:50,120 --> 00:53:52,750
Bit me directly in the buttocks.

720
00:53:53,200 --> 00:53:57,660
They said it was a million-dollar wound,
but the Army must keep that money,

721
00:53:58,360 --> 00:54:01,590
‘cause I still ain't seen a nickel
of that million dollars.

722
00:54:02,840 --> 00:54:05,820
The only good thing
about being wounded in the buttocks

723
00:54:06,320 --> 00:54:07,790
is the ice cream.

724
00:54:08,080 --> 00:54:10,290
They gave me all the ice cream
! could eat.

725
00:54:10,680 --> 00:54:11,799
And guess what?

726
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:14,640
A good friend of mine
was in the bed right next door.

727
00:54:17,160 --> 00:54:19,720
Lieutenant Dan,
I got you some ice cream.

728
00:54:22,400 --> 00:54:24,190
Lieutenant Dan, ice cream.

729
00:54:35,720 --> 00:54:37,609
It's time for your bath, Lieutenant.

730
00:54:46,080 --> 00:54:47,200
Harper!

731
00:54:50,440 --> 00:54:52,510
Cooper, Larson,

732
00:54:54,920 --> 00:54:56,040
Webster,

733
00:54:57,520 --> 00:55:00,470
-Gump. Gump.
-I'm Forrest Gump.

734
00:55:04,320 --> 00:55:07,060
Kyle, Nichols,

735
00:55:09,560 --> 00:55:14,549
McMill, Johnson, Tyler,

736
00:55:16,560 --> 00:55:17,750
Holiday...

737
00:55:24,280 --> 00:55:26,210
Surprise, surprise, surprise!

738
00:55:29,680 --> 00:55:31,750
Gump, how can you watch
that stupid shit?

739
00:55:32,120 --> 00:55:33,450
-From the DMZ to the Delta...
-Turn it off!

740
00:55:33,720 --> 00:55:36,490
...you are tuned to the
American Forces Vietnam Network.

