1042
01:18:53,520 --> 01:18:56,190
! didn't stay home for long,
because I'd made a promise to Bubba,

1043
01:18:56,640 --> 01:18:58,530
and I always try to keep my promise.

1044
01:18:58,880 --> 01:19:00,140
So, ! went on down to Bayou La Batre

1045
01:19:00,400 --> 01:19:03,589
to meet Bubba's family
and make their introduction.

1046
01:19:04,120 --> 01:19:07,210
Are you crazy, or just plain stupid?

1047
01:19:08,320 --> 01:19:10,210
Stupid is as stupid does, Mrs Blue.

1048
01:19:10,560 --> 01:19:11,720
I guess.

1049
01:19:12,840 --> 01:19:15,820
And, of course,
! paid my respect to Bubba himself.

1050
01:19:18,200 --> 01:19:20,340
Hey, Bubba, it's me, Forrest Gump.

1051
01:19:23,640 --> 01:19:27,050
l remember everything you said,
and I got it all figured out.

1052
01:19:30,160 --> 01:19:36,309
I'm taking the $24,560
and 47 cents that I got...

1053
01:19:37,760 --> 01:19:40,780
Or, that’s left after a new hair cut
and a new suit,

1054
01:19:41,280 --> 01:19:42,929
and I took Mama out
to a real fancy dinner,

1055
01:19:43,240 --> 01:19:45,980
and ! bought a bus ticket
and three Dr Peppers.

1056
01:19:46,880 --> 01:19:48,390
Tell me something.

1057
01:19:49,600 --> 01:19:51,390
Are you stupid or something?

1058
01:19:51,720 --> 01:19:53,440
Stupid is as stupid does, sir.

1059
01:19:53,760 --> 01:19:56,250
Well, that's what's left after me saying,

1060
01:19:57,480 --> 01:19:59,269
“When I was in China
on the All-America Ping-Pong team,

1061
01:19:59,600 --> 01:20:02,830
"I just loved playing Ping-Pong with
my Flex-O-Light Ping-Pong paddle,”

1062
01:20:03,360 --> 01:20:04,410
which everybody knows isn't true,

1063
01:20:04,640 --> 01:20:05,760
but Mama says it's just a little white lie

1064
01:20:06,000 --> 01:20:07,860
so it wouldn't hurt nobody.

1065
01:20:09,480 --> 01:20:14,469
So, anyway, I'm putting all that on gas,
ropes and new nets

1066
01:20:15,880 --> 01:20:17,320
and a brand-new shrimping boat.

1067
01:20:38,360 --> 01:20:41,099
Now, Bubba had told me everything
he knew about shrimping,

1068
01:20:41,560 --> 01:20:43,520
but you know what I found out?

1069
01:20:45,360 --> 01:20:47,320
Shrimping is tough.

1070
01:20:49,760 --> 01:20:51,300
I only caught five.

1071
01:20:51,600 --> 01:20:54,410
A couple more,
you could have yourself a cocktail.

1072
01:20:58,000 --> 01:20:59,470
Hey, you ever think
about naming this old boat?

1073
01:20:59,760 --> 01:21:02,040
It's bad luck
to have a boat without a name.

1074
01:21:04,640 --> 01:21:08,710
I'd never named a boat before,
but there was only one I could think of,

1075
01:21:10,400 --> 01:21:13,099
the most beautiful name
in the wide world.

1076
01:21:33,640 --> 01:21:36,030
Now, I hadn’t heard from Jenny
in a long while,

1077
01:21:36,440 --> 01:21:38,580
but f thought about her a lot,

1078
01:21:38,960 --> 01:21:41,840
and I hoped that whatever
she was doing made her happy.

1079
01:23:24,200 --> 01:23:26,370
! thought about Jenny ail the time.

1080
01:23:50,280 --> 01:23:51,259
Hey!

1081
01:24:14,280 --> 01:24:18,210
Lieutenant Dan,
what are you doing here?

1082
01:24:18,880 --> 01:24:22,180
Well, thought I'd try out my sea legs.

1083
01:24:22,720 --> 01:24:25,880
But you ain't got no legs,
Lieutenant Dan.

1084
01:24:26,400 --> 01:24:28,290
Yes, I know that.

1085
01:24:28,920 --> 01:24:30,640
You wrote me a letter, you idiot.

1086
01:24:30,960 --> 01:24:34,820
Well, well. Captain Forrest Gump.
l had to see this for myself.

1087
01:24:36,920 --> 01:24:42,720
And I told you if you were ever
a shrimp boat captain

1088
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:45,810
that I'd be your first mate.
Well, here 1 am.

1089
01:24:46,200 --> 01:24:48,830
-lam a man of my word.
-Okay.

1090
01:24:49,280 --> 01:24:52,650
Yeah, but don't you be thinking that
I'm going to be calling you "sir."

1091
01:24:53,200 --> 01:24:54,320
No, sir.

1092
01:25:03,000 --> 01:25:04,890
That's my boat.

1093
01:25:07,680 --> 01:25:12,280
Il have a feeling if we head due east,
we'll find some shrimp,

1094
01:25:13,000 --> 01:25:14,370
so take a left.

1095
01:25:15,880 --> 01:25:18,370
-Take a left!
-Which way?

1096
01:25:18,800 --> 01:25:21,050
Over there! They're over there!

1097
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:25,190
-Get on the wheel and take a left!
-Okay.

1098
01:25:26,840 --> 01:25:30,280
Gump, what are you doing?
Take a left! Left!

1099
01:25:33,080 --> 01:25:36,100
That's where we're going
to find those shrimp, my boy!

1100
01:25:38,080 --> 01:25:39,160
That's where we'll find them.

1101
01:25:51,760 --> 01:25:55,200
-Still no shrimp, Lieutenant Dan.
-Okay, so I was wrong.

1102
01:25:56,400 --> 01:25:59,099
How are we going to find them?

1103
01:25:59,560 --> 01:26:01,700
Well, maybe you should
just pray for shrimp.

1104
01:26:08,320 --> 01:26:10,570
So, ! went to church every Sunday.

1105
01:26:12,120 --> 01:26:13,800
Sometimes Lieutenant Dan came, too,

1106
01:26:14,120 --> 01:26:16,680
though I think
he left the praying up to me.

1107
01:26:31,840 --> 01:26:35,560
-No shrimp.
-Where the hell's this God of yours?

1108
01:26:36,840 --> 01:26:41,690
It's funny Lieutenant Dan said that,
‘cause right then, God showed up.

1109
01:26:58,520 --> 01:27:02,590
-You'll never sink this boat!
-Now, me, ! was scared,

1110
01:27:03,240 --> 01:27:05,840
but Lieutenant Dan, he was mad.

1111
01:27:06,280 --> 01:27:07,400
Come on!

1112
01:27:10,560 --> 01:27:14,950
You call this a storm?
Come on, you son of a bitch!

1113
01:27:17,600 --> 01:27:21,320
It's time for a showdown! You and me!

1114
01:27:21,920 --> 01:27:25,220
I'm right here! Come and get me!

1115
01:27:27,360 --> 01:27:30,660
You'll never sink this boat!

1116
01:27:33,080 --> 01:27:34,900
Hurricane Carmen
came through here yesterday,

1117
01:27:35,240 --> 01:27:37,410
destroying nearly everything in its path.

1118
01:27:37,800 --> 01:27:39,940
And as in other towns
up and down the coast,

1119
01:27:40,360 --> 01:27:42,360
Bayou La Batre’s
entire shrimping industry

1120
01:27:42,720 --> 01:27:45,980
has fallen victim to Carmen
and has been left in utter ruin.

1121
01:27:46,560 --> 01:27:49,230
Speaking with local officials,
this reporter has learned,

1122
01:27:49,680 --> 01:27:52,560
in fact, only one shrimping boat
actually survived the storm.

1123
01:27:53,360 --> 01:27:55,530
Louise. Louise, there's Forrest.

1124
01:27:56,520 --> 01:27:58,240
After that, shrimping was easy.

1125
01:28:03,920 --> 01:28:06,550
Since people still needed
them shrimps for shrimp cocktails

1126
01:28:07,000 --> 01:28:10,440
and barbecues and all,
and we were the only boat left standing,

1127
01:28:11,080 --> 01:28:13,850
Bubba-Gump Shrimp's what they got.

1128
01:28:14,320 --> 01:28:18,179
We got a whole bunch of boats,
12 Jenny's,

1129
01:28:18,800 --> 01:28:21,710
a big old warehouse. We even have
hats that say "Bubba-Gump" on them.

1130
01:28:22,440 --> 01:28:25,210
Bubba-Gump Shrimp.
It's a household name.

1131
01:28:25,840 --> 01:28:27,280
Hold on there, boy.

1132
01:28:27,560 --> 01:28:31,420
Are you telling me you're the owner of
the Bubba-Gump Shrimp Corporation?

1133
01:28:32,080 --> 01:28:34,610
Yes, sir. We got more money
than Davy Crockett.

1134
01:28:36,480 --> 01:28:39,889
Boy, I heard some whoppers in my time,
but that tops them all.

1135
01:28:43,000 --> 01:28:45,320
We was sitting next to a millionaire.

1136
01:28:49,000 --> 01:28:52,900
Well, I thought it was a very lovely story,

1137
01:28:53,880 --> 01:28:57,780
and you tell it so well,
with such enthusiasm.

1138
01:28:59,960 --> 01:29:02,210
Would you like to see
what Lieutenant Dan looks like?

1139
01:29:02,600 --> 01:29:03,900
Well, yes, I would.

1140
01:29:09,000 --> 01:29:10,720
That's him right there.

1141
01:29:13,080 --> 01:29:14,940
And let me tell you something
about Lieutenant Dan...

1142
01:29:16,320 --> 01:29:17,190
Forrest,

1143
01:29:22,680 --> 01:29:25,030
I never thanked you for saving my life.

1144
01:29:50,320 --> 01:29:55,590
He never actually said so,
but I think he made his peace with God.

1145
01:30:03,680 --> 01:30:05,570
For the second time in 17 days,

1146
01:30:05,920 --> 01:30:08,830
President Ford escaped
possible assassination today.

1147
01:30:09,320 --> 01:30:10,440
Base to Jenny 1.

1148
01:30:10,680 --> 01:30:13,560
-Base to Jenny 1.
-Jenny 1. Go, Margo.

1149
01:30:14,080 --> 01:30:15,410
Forrest has a phone call.

1150
01:30:15,680 --> 01:30:17,710
Yeah, well, you'll have to tell them
to call him back.

1151
01:30:18,080 --> 01:30:20,920
-He is indisposed at the moment.
-His mama's sick.

1152
01:30:41,200 --> 01:30:43,200
-Where's Mama?
-She's upstairs.

1153
01:30:46,200 --> 01:30:47,809
Hi, Forrest.

1154
01:30:48,960 --> 01:30:51,130
-I'll see you tomorrow.
-All right.

1155
01:30:57,800 --> 01:31:00,470
We sure got you straightened out,
didn't we, boy?

1156
01:31:11,760 --> 01:31:15,060
-What's the matter, Mama?
-I'm dying, Forrest.

1157
01:31:18,720 --> 01:31:20,750
Come on in, sit down over here.

1158
01:31:34,760 --> 01:31:37,710
-Why are you dying, Mama?
-It's my time.

1159
01:31:39,120 --> 01:31:40,700
It's just my time.

1160
01:31:42,280 --> 01:31:45,929
Now, don't you be afraid, sweetheart.

1161
01:31:47,840 --> 01:31:50,050
Death is just a part of life,

1162
01:31:51,080 --> 01:31:53,290
something we're all destined to do.

1163
01:31:55,360 --> 01:31:59,049
I didn't know it,
but I was destined to be your mama.

1164
01:32:00,360 --> 01:32:03,480
-I did the best I could.
-You did good, Mama.

1165
01:32:04,600 --> 01:32:08,950
Well, I happen to believe
you make your own destiny.

1166
01:32:11,000 --> 01:32:13,700
You have to do the best
with what God gave you.

1167
01:32:17,800 --> 01:32:19,590
What's my destiny, Mama?

1168
01:32:21,920 --> 01:32:24,900
You're going to have
to figure that out for yourself.

1169
01:32:26,240 --> 01:32:28,769
Life is a box of chocolates, Forrest.

1170
01:32:29,200 --> 01:32:31,019
You never know
what you're going to get.

1171
01:32:31,360 --> 01:32:35,120
Mama always had a way of explaining
things so I could understand them.

1172
01:32:35,720 --> 01:32:37,790
I will miss you, Forrest.

1173
01:32:39,520 --> 01:32:42,960
She had got the cancer
and died on a Tuesday.

1174
01:32:44,880 --> 01:32:47,690
! bought her a new hat
with little flowers on it.

1175
01:32:51,000 --> 01:32:53,740
And that's all 1 have to say about that.

1176
01:33:00,720 --> 01:33:02,650
Didn't you say you were waiting
for the number seven bus?

1177
01:33:03,000 --> 01:33:05,350
There'll be another one along shortly.

1178
01:33:09,320 --> 01:33:12,370
Now, because I had been a football star,
and a war hero,

1179
01:33:12,880 --> 01:33:15,480
and a national celebrity,
and a shrimping boat captain,

1180
01:33:16,320 --> 01:33:19,059
and a college graduate,
the city fathers of Greenbow, Alabama

1181
01:33:19,520 --> 01:33:22,120
decided to get together
and offered me a fine job.

1182
01:33:23,960 --> 01:33:27,050
So, ! never went back to work
for Lieutenant Dan,

1183
01:33:27,560 --> 01:33:29,880
though he did take care
of my Bubba-Gump money.

1184
01:33:30,280 --> 01:33:34,179
He got me invested
in some kind of fruit company.

1185
01:33:34,800 --> 01:33:35,920
And so then, ! got a call from him saying

1186
01:33:36,160 --> 01:33:38,440
we don't have to worry about money
no more, and I said,

1187
01:33:39,800 --> 01:33:41,730
“That's good. One less thing.”

1188
01:33:44,920 --> 01:33:47,900
Now, Mama said there’s only
so much fortune a man really needs,

1189
01:33:49,320 --> 01:33:51,740
and the rest is just for showing off.

1190
01:33:52,160 --> 01:33:55,420
So, ! gave a whole bunch of it
to the Foursquare gospel church,

1191
01:33:58,360 --> 01:34:01,519
and I gave a whole bunch to the
Bayou La Batre fishing hospital.

1192
01:34:05,000 --> 01:34:08,860
And even though Bubba was dead
and Lieutenant Dan said ! was nuts,

1193
01:34:09,480 --> 01:34:11,690
1 gave Bubba’s mama Bubba's share.

1194
01:34:16,040 --> 01:34:17,510
You know what?

1195
01:34:18,880 --> 01:34:21,440
She didn’t have to work
in nobody's kitchen no more.

1196
01:34:21,880 --> 01:34:23,180
That smells wonderful.

1197
01:34:24,240 --> 01:34:27,540
And ‘cause ! was a gazillionaire
and I liked doing it so much,

1198
01:34:28,080 --> 01:34:30,010
! cut that grass for free.

1199
01:34:33,920 --> 01:34:36,340
But at night time
when there was nothing to do

1200
01:34:36,760 --> 01:34:38,760
and the house was ail empty,

1201
01:34:40,000 --> 01:34:42,000
I'd always think of Jenny.

1202
01:35:43,360 --> 01:35:46,030
And then, she was there.

1203
01:36:18,040 --> 01:36:20,710
-Hello, Forrest.
-Hello, Jenny.

1204
01:36:32,160 --> 01:36:34,370
Jenny came back and stayed with me.

1205
01:36:36,240 --> 01:36:39,330
Maybe it was because
she had nowhere else to go,

1206
01:36:39,840 --> 01:36:43,000
or maybe it was because she was
so tired, ‘cause she went to bed

1207
01:36:43,520 --> 01:36:46,850
and slept and slept,
like she hadn't slept in years.

1208
01:36:48,560 --> 01:36:50,490
It was wonderful having her home.

1209
01:36:52,000 --> 01:36:56,350
Every day we’d take a walk and
I'd jabber on like a monkey in a tree,

1210
01:36:57,040 --> 01:36:59,140
and she'd listen about Ping-Ponging,
and shrimping,

1211
01:36:59,520 --> 01:37:03,170
and Mama making a trip up to heaven.
! did all the talking.

1212
01:37:03,760 --> 01:37:06,780
Jenny most of the time was real quiet.

1213
01:37:45,440 --> 01:37:48,349
How could you do this?

1214
01:38:23,960 --> 01:38:26,770
Sometimes !I guess there
just aren't enough rocks.

1215
01:38:29,280 --> 01:38:33,070
! never really knew why she came back,
but I didn’t care.

1216
01:38:33,760 --> 01:38:37,380
It was like olden times.
